sortium">https://github.com/CICE-Consortium</a>. Blockley and Vancoppenolle received funding through the contributions of their institutions to the NEMO consortium and from the European Unions Horizon 2020 research and innovation programme under grant agreement No 824084 (IS-ENES3), which, together with the U.S. Department of Energys Office of Science Biological and Environmental Research programs, funded the workshop: Towards defining a cutting-edge future for sea ice modelling, the inspiration for this paper. Rasmussen and Ribergaard were funded by Denmark through the National Centre for Climate Research and by the SALIENSEAS project, part of the ERA4CS programme, which is co-funded by the Innovation Fund Denmark and the Horizon 2020 Framework Programme of the European Union (Grant 690462). Zhang was supported by NASA grant NNX17AD27G, and Schweiger by ONR grant N00014-17-1-3162. This work is a contribution to the National Science and Engineering Research Council - Discovery Program and the NSF Office of Polar Program grant # 1928126, awarded to Tremblay.</p></div></div></section><section aria-labelledby="author-information" data-title="Author information"><div class="c-article-section" id="author-information-section"><h2 class="c-article-section__title js-section-title js-c-reading-companion-sections-item" id="author-information">Author information</h2><div class="c-article-section__content" id="author-information-content"><h3 class="c-article__sub-heading" id="affiliations">Affiliations</h3><ol class="c-article-author-affiliation__list"><li id="Aff1"><p class="c-article-author-affiliation__address">MS-B216, Los Alamos National Laboratory, Los Alamos, NM, 87545, USA</p><p class="c-article-author-affiliation__authors-list">Elizabeth Hunke</p></li><li id="Aff2"><p class="c-article-author-affiliation__address">U.S. Naval Research Laboratory Stennis Space Center, Stennis, MS, USA</p><p class="c-article-author-affiliation__authors-list">Richard Allard</p></li><li id="